   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The earth busbars can be located at the top <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(A)</b> or the bottom <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(B)</b>. Each earth busbar is labeled with
a protective earth symbol.</p>
            <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">All earth busbars
in the system must be connected to the protective earth.</note>
            <fig class="- topic/fig ">
               <image href="../Images/Earthing_Busbar_Top-Bottom_0000415585.svg"
                      scope="local"
                      placement="inline"
                      class="- topic/image "/>
            </fig>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Connect Top Earth Busbars</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the gland plates have all the required holes drilled
and that they are firmly fixed on the roof.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the earth cable is connected to the protective earth
at the installation location.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Pull the earth cable <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> through the already drilled
hole in the top gland plate.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Attach the earth cable <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(C)</b> to the top earth busbar <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(D)</b> with the fastening set <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">(E)</b>. Tighten to 16 Nm (11.8
lb-ft).</p>
                  <note id="busbar_fastening_set" class="- topic/note ">The busbar fastenings sets
are typically already attached to the busbar.</note>
               </li>
            </ol>
